<h2>iii. Related Disciplines</h2>
<div class="smallWords">
	<div class="centered" style="margin:0px auto;text-align:center;">
	<img src="bio103/biograph/img/biograph.jpg" alt="Related Disciplines"><br />
		<span class="captions" style="text-align:center;">Figure A-2. A graphical representation of Plant Biology study field relations</span>
	</div>
<ol type="i">
	<li><span class="boldened">Biochemistry-</span> called biological chemistry, is the study of chemical processes within, and relating to, living organisms.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Biophysics</span>- interdisciplinary science using methods of, and theories from, physics to study biological systems.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Biostatistics</span>- application of statistics to a wide range of topics in biology.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Bioengineering</span>- application of concepts and methods of biology to solve real-world problems related to the life sciences and/or the application thereof, using engineering’s own analytical and synthetic methodologies.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Biotechnology</span>- the use of living systems and organisms to develop or make useful products, or any technological application that uses biological systems.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Bioinformatics</span>- the use of computer science, mathematics and information theory to model and analyze biological systems, specially systems involving genetic material.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Agriculture</span>- the cultivation of animals, plants, fungi, and other life forms for food, fiber, biofuel, drugs and other products used to sustain and enhance human life.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Medicine</span>- practice of the diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of disease.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Medical Technology</span>- subset of health technology, encompasses a wide range of healthcare products and is used to diagnose, monitor or treat diseases or medical conditions affecting humans.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Nursing</span>- health care sector focusing on the care of individuals, families, and communities so they may attain, maintain, or recover optimal health and quality of life.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Forestry</span>- the science and art  of creating, managing, using, conserving, and repairing forests and associated resources to meet desired goals, needs, and values for human benefit.</li>
	<li><span class="boldened">Pharmacology</span> - the science of drugs including their origin, composition, properties, interactions, toxicology, therapy: pharmacokinetics, the movement of the drugs within the organism’s body; pharmacodynamics- the effect of the drugs on living organisms; and medicinal uses.</li>
</ol>
</div>

